-f[suppress most error messages]
-R[change files and directories recursively]
-v[output a diagnostic for every file processed]
-h[operate on symlinks them self]
-L[follow all symlinks]
-H[follow symlinks on the command line]
-P[do not follow symlinks (default)]
-C[returns false if any of the named files have ACLs]
-N[remove ACLs from specified files]
-E[read ACL info from stdin as a sequential list of ACEs]
-i[removes inherited bit from all entries in named files ACLs]
-I[removes all inherited entries from named files ACLs]
